ty\n| alliance3 = {{legend2|{{National Democratic Alliance (India)/meta/color}}|[[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| leaders_seat3 = {{dash}}\n| last_election3 = 1\n| seats_needed3 = \n| seats3 = \n| seat_change3 = \n| popular_vote3 = \n| percentage3 = \n| swing3 = \n\n| map_caption = Kerala Assembly Seats\n| title = [[Chief Minister of Kerala|Chief Minister]]\n| posttitle = Elected [[Chief Minister of Kerala|Chief Minister]]\n| before_election = [[Pinarayi Vijayan]]\n| before_party = Communist Party of India (Marxist)\n| after_election= TBD\n| after_party =\n| party_colour = \n| map = \n\n}}\n\n\n\n'''Legislative Assembly elections''' are scheduled to be held in [[Kerala]] in May 2021.<ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/opinion/columns/bjp-cms-assembly-elections-narendra-modi-amit-shah-6189263/</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn the [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election|previous elections]] in 2016, the [[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|Left Democratic Front (LDF)]] won the election, defeating the incumbent [[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|United Democratic Front (UDF)]], led by the [[Indian National Congress|Indian National Congress (INC)]], which could only win 47 seats in the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/assembly-elections/live-assembly-poll-results-counting-of-votes-in-tamil-nadu-kerala-assam-west-bengal-puducherry/story-nmYc0zJVdyQ25jUFRZsGrN.html|title=As it happened: TMC, AIADMK retain power; BJP takes Assam, Left Kerala|last=|first=|date=19 May 2016|newspaper=Hindustan Times|accessdate=11 August 2019}}</ref>\n==Schedule==\n\n== Parties and alliances ==\nThere are two major political Alliances in Kerala. The [[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|United Democratic Front]] (UDF) is the coalition of centrist and centre-right parties led by the [[Indian National Congress]]. The [[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|Left Democratic Front]] (LDF) is the coalition of left wing and centre-left parties, led by the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]] (CPI(M)).\n\n=== {{legend2|{{United Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}|[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|United Democratic Front]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}} ===\n\nIt is an alliance of central-wing political parties in the state, created by the prominent  [[Indian National Congress|INC]] party leader [[K. Karunakaran]] in the 1970s.\n\n{|class=\"sortable\" width=\"40%\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"6\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\" \n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" | No.\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Party !! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Flag\n!style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Symbol!!style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Photo!!style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Leader\n!style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Seats contested\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''1.'''\n| [[Indian National Congress]]\n| [[File:Flag of the Indian National Congress.svg|50px]]\n| [[File:Hand INC.svg|42x42px|alt=|center|frameless]]\n|[[File:Shri_Mullappally_Ramachandran_taking_over_the_charge_of_the_Minister_of_State_for_Home_Affairs,_in_New_Delhi_on_May_30,_2009.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|125x125px]]\n| [[Mullappally Ramachandran]]\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Indian Union Muslim League/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''2.'''\n| [[Indian Union Muslim League]]\n| [[File:Flag of the Indian Union Muslim League.svg|50px]]  \n| [[File:Indian Election Symbol Lader.png|50px]]\n|[[File:Sayed_Hyderali_Shihab_Thangal_BNC.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|125x125px]]\n| [[Sayed Hyderali Shihab Thangal]]\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Kerala Congress (Mani)/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''3.'''\n| [[Kerala Congress (M)]]\n| [[File:Kerala-Congress-flag.svg|50px]] \n| [[File:Indian election symbol two leaves.svg|50px]]\n| [[File:P.J Joseph.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|125x125px]]\n| [[P. J. Joseph]]\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Revolutionary Socialist Party (India)/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''4.'''\n| [[Revolutionary Socialist Party (India)|Revolutionary Socialist Party]]\n| [[File:RSP-flag.svg|50px]] \n| [[File:Indian Election Symbol Spade and Stoker.png|50px]]\n| [[File:A_A_Azeez.JPG|alt=|center|frameless|125x125px]]\n| [[A.A. Aziz]]\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Kerala Congress (Jacob)/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''5.'''\n| [[Kerala Congress (Jacob)]] || [[File:Kerala-Congress-flag.svg|50px]] \n| \n| [[File:Anoop jacob.JPG|alt=|center|frameless|125x125px]]\n| [[Anoop Jacob]]\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Communist Marxist Party/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''6.'''\n| [[Communist Marxist Party (John)]] ||[[File:CMP-banner.svg|50px]]  \n|\n|\n| CP John\n|\n|-\n|! style=\"text-align:center; background:{{Janathipathiya Samrakshana Samithy/meta/color}};color:white\"|'''7.'''\n|[[Janathipathiya Samrakshana Samithy|Janathipathiya Samrakshana Samithy (National)]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Alex Dominic\n|\n\n|}\n\n=== {{legend2|{{Left Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}|[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|Left Democratic Front]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}} ===\n\nIt is a coalition of [[Left-wing politics|left-wing]] political parties in the state. It is one of the two major political coalitions in Kerala, the other being the UDF each of which has been in power alternatively for the last four decades. LDF is now in power. The coalition consists of [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]], [[Communist Party of India|CPI]] and a variety of other smaller parties.\n\n{|class=\"sortable\" width=\"40%\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"6\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; align=\"center\"; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collaps